WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.565
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:05.565 --> 00:00:07.440
MICHAEL R. VIRARDI: Good
afternoon, everyone.

00:00:07.440 --> 00:00:08.870
Thank you for being present.

00:00:08.870 --> 00:00:11.670
Happy women's day to all
the ladies in the audience.

00:00:11.670 --> 00:00:15.940
And it is a pleasure and an
honor being here at Google.

00:00:15.940 --> 00:00:20.250
It was always on
the 25th of December

00:00:20.250 --> 00:00:25.990
that my late father Rolando used
to recite the exact same story

00:00:25.990 --> 00:00:31.790
year in and year out to my elder
brother Giovanni and myself.

00:00:31.790 --> 00:00:33.670
It wasn't one of
his own stories.

00:00:33.670 --> 00:00:36.250
It didn't stem from
his own experiences.

00:00:36.250 --> 00:00:38.140
But it was a story
that was related

00:00:38.140 --> 00:00:43.420
to him by a former
mentor of his, Dr. Rossi,

00:00:43.420 --> 00:00:48.020
when my father used to work at
the Cyprus embassy in London.

00:00:48.020 --> 00:00:52.710
The story was about a former
Undersecretary of Defense

00:00:52.710 --> 00:00:56.570
and that former Undersecretary
of Defense was invited,

00:00:56.570 --> 00:01:01.210
for the second year running,
at the same conference.

00:01:01.210 --> 00:01:05.980
As he took up the podium, he
was holding a styrofoam cup

00:01:05.980 --> 00:01:07.810
with coffee in his hand.

00:01:07.810 --> 00:01:13.230
And before he started speaking,
he went off script, took a sip,

00:01:13.230 --> 00:01:17.290
smiled, turned, looked
at the audience and said,

00:01:17.290 --> 00:01:20.400
I want to talk to you
about this styrofoam cup.

00:01:20.400 --> 00:01:25.010
Last year, I was the
Undersecretary of Defense.

00:01:25.010 --> 00:01:28.260
I flew here business class.

00:01:28.260 --> 00:01:31.000
A limousine was waiting
for me at the airport

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:33.160
to drive me to my hotel.

00:01:33.160 --> 00:01:35.510
They already checked me in.

00:01:35.510 --> 00:01:39.050
The next day, there was
another limousine waiting

00:01:39.050 --> 00:01:41.830
to bring me to this venue.

00:01:41.830 --> 00:01:43.900
They escorted me
to the green room,

00:01:43.900 --> 00:01:45.400
and the green room
is the room where

00:01:45.400 --> 00:01:49.930
all speakers meet and prepare
before they take the stage.

00:01:49.930 --> 00:01:53.330
And when I asked for
something to drink,

00:01:53.330 --> 00:01:58.080
they brought me coffee
in a ceramic cup.

00:01:58.080 --> 00:02:01.875
This year, I'm no longer the
Undersecretary of Defense.

00:02:04.570 --> 00:02:05.950
I came.

00:02:05.950 --> 00:02:07.810
I flew economy class.

00:02:07.810 --> 00:02:12.700
I took a taxi from the airport
all the way to my hotel.

00:02:12.700 --> 00:02:17.020
I checked myself in
and it took 15 minutes.

00:02:17.020 --> 00:02:21.840
The next day, I took another
taxi to come to this venue.

00:02:21.840 --> 00:02:25.530
And because I couldn't remember
where the green room was,

00:02:25.530 --> 00:02:29.790
I asked them to escort me, and
they gave me mere directions

00:02:29.790 --> 00:02:32.340
how to get there.

00:02:32.340 --> 00:02:34.650
Then I asked for
something to drink.

00:02:34.650 --> 00:02:36.840
And they showed me
the vending machine.

00:02:36.840 --> 00:02:39.460
And they said take
a styrofoam cup,

00:02:39.460 --> 00:02:42.690
and serve yourself
whatever you like.

00:02:42.690 --> 00:02:46.390
He turns, looks at
the audience and says,

00:02:46.390 --> 00:02:50.400
we all deserve a styrofoam cup.

00:02:50.400 --> 00:02:53.860
The ceramic cup was
never meant for us.

00:02:53.860 --> 00:02:59.560
It was meant for the position
that I was holding at the time.

00:02:59.560 --> 00:03:04.960
So as you gain fame, as you
gain fortune, positions,

00:03:04.960 --> 00:03:09.890
or possessions, people
will open up doors for you.

00:03:09.890 --> 00:03:14.170
They will refer to
you as sir and madam.

00:03:14.170 --> 00:03:15.910
They will bring gifts.

00:03:15.910 --> 00:03:18.560
And when you ask for
something to drink,

00:03:18.560 --> 00:03:23.760
they will bring your coffee
or your tea in a ceramic cup.

00:03:23.760 --> 00:03:28.110
But because time
doesn't stand still,

00:03:28.110 --> 00:03:30.590
we all deserve a styrofoam cup.

00:03:33.220 --> 00:03:37.090
And as the former
Undersecretary of Defense

00:03:37.090 --> 00:03:43.285
found out the hard way, we, too,
should be alerted to the fact

00:03:43.285 --> 00:03:46.510
and to the possibility
that we might not

00:03:46.510 --> 00:03:51.690
be our current position
or our possessions.

00:03:51.690 --> 00:03:55.020
Who we really are, as
today's title suggests,

00:03:55.020 --> 00:03:59.010
which is Finding
Your Inner Compass,

00:03:59.010 --> 00:04:01.950
is that internal compass,
when you strip away

00:04:01.950 --> 00:04:06.240
positions or possessions
that will guide you

00:04:06.240 --> 00:04:10.560
through challenging and
difficult moments in business

00:04:10.560 --> 00:04:13.400
and in life.

00:04:13.400 --> 00:04:19.310
Today, my dear friends, I will
relay five personal stories.

00:04:19.310 --> 00:04:23.890
And each story carries
a valuable lesson.

00:04:23.890 --> 00:04:27.670
That's the lessons that power
my internal compass and helped

00:04:27.670 --> 00:04:30.500
me navigate through
the professional

00:04:30.500 --> 00:04:32.890
and the personal world.

00:04:32.890 --> 00:04:36.710
I hope that by the
end of this speech,

00:04:36.710 --> 00:04:39.430
these same stories and
the underlying messages

00:04:39.430 --> 00:04:44.140
from these stories will help
power your internal compass

00:04:44.140 --> 00:04:47.020
and help you navigate
better in your life.

00:04:47.020 --> 00:04:50.540
So they make the road
more smooth in order

00:04:50.540 --> 00:04:56.250
to reach for that elusive
word, which is called success.

00:04:56.250 --> 00:04:58.770
Three disclaimers to make--

00:04:58.770 --> 00:05:03.200
each and every lesson
starts with the letter H,

00:05:03.200 --> 00:05:05.760
as you will see from each story.

00:05:05.760 --> 00:05:09.330
Second disclaimer--
there are no PowerPoints.

00:05:09.330 --> 00:05:13.060
Unlike 95% of my
keynote speaking,

00:05:13.060 --> 00:05:14.550
there are no PowerPoints.

00:05:14.550 --> 00:05:17.610
Because I do not
believe that a slide

00:05:17.610 --> 00:05:21.780
can depict internal
compasses and values, as well

00:05:21.780 --> 00:05:27.060
as a vivid story which
carries an underlying message.

00:05:27.060 --> 00:05:28.390
And disclaimer number three--

00:05:32.970 --> 00:05:38.220
the third story, which
happened 13 years ago in 2006,

00:05:38.220 --> 00:05:41.460
I've never ever before
said this story in front

00:05:41.460 --> 00:05:43.410
of a professional audience.

00:05:43.410 --> 00:05:46.500
I only once
mentioned this story,

00:05:46.500 --> 00:05:51.420
and that was on the
9th of October 2018

00:05:51.420 --> 00:05:54.450
as I was lecturing at University
College London in front

00:05:54.450 --> 00:05:56.530
of 300 students.

00:05:56.530 --> 00:05:57.730
So let's begin.

00:05:57.730 --> 00:06:01.800
And let me take
you back to 1997.

00:06:01.800 --> 00:06:04.200
That was the year that
I completed my studies

00:06:04.200 --> 00:06:05.730
in the United Kingdom.

00:06:05.730 --> 00:06:07.770
I'd done my BA and
my master's degree.

00:06:07.770 --> 00:06:12.570
And like any good Cypriot boy
who has a flourishing business,

00:06:12.570 --> 00:06:14.430
I went back to the
island, back to Cyprus

00:06:14.430 --> 00:06:15.763
to work for the family business.

00:06:18.430 --> 00:06:20.392
All newcomers at
our family business,

00:06:20.392 --> 00:06:22.600
which was called Virardi--
it's still called Virardi,

00:06:22.600 --> 00:06:25.420
we deal with catering
equipment and tabletop supplies

00:06:25.420 --> 00:06:29.180
for the HoReCa industry, the
HoReCa industry is hotels,

00:06:29.180 --> 00:06:31.720
restaurants, and
catering institutions--

00:06:31.720 --> 00:06:34.000
had to go through
an induction course.

00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:36.190
And that induction
course started

00:06:36.190 --> 00:06:39.490
from my late father's office.

00:06:39.490 --> 00:06:43.530
And I, too, had to go
through the same procedure.

00:06:43.530 --> 00:06:47.400
That was what I
called my PhD degree.

00:06:47.400 --> 00:06:50.130
Only it didn't last five years.

00:06:50.130 --> 00:06:52.800
It lasted five minutes.

00:06:52.800 --> 00:06:58.140
My father gave me two
valuable pieces of advice.

00:06:58.140 --> 00:07:03.640
For the first piece of advice,
my father took a pencil.

00:07:03.640 --> 00:07:05.690
And he took a sharpener.

00:07:05.690 --> 00:07:15.880
And he said, Michael,
I've sharpened your edge.

00:07:15.880 --> 00:07:20.900
I paid your [INAUDIBLE] and
I paid for your tuition.

00:07:20.900 --> 00:07:25.870
But if you leave a pencil
standing on its own,

00:07:25.870 --> 00:07:28.090
it will fall.

00:07:28.090 --> 00:07:31.330
Go out there, son,
and find the hand

00:07:31.330 --> 00:07:34.880
that will keep you standing.

00:07:34.880 --> 00:07:36.410
The hand that will
keep you standing

00:07:36.410 --> 00:07:40.070
was an analogy for the
mentors in my life,

00:07:40.070 --> 00:07:42.380
for the trusted
advisors, the likes

00:07:42.380 --> 00:07:45.530
of your former colleague
[INAUDIBLE] was escorting me

00:07:45.530 --> 00:07:50.090
here, all the mistakes
that I've done in my life

00:07:50.090 --> 00:07:53.090
and all the failures
that I've encountered.

00:07:53.090 --> 00:07:56.060
Because as the saying
goes, when you lose,

00:07:56.060 --> 00:07:57.080
don't lose the lesson.

00:08:00.970 --> 00:08:03.790
And I owe a very big thank
you to all the people

00:08:03.790 --> 00:08:08.780
who turned me down and all those
who believed in me to hire me.

00:08:08.780 --> 00:08:13.030
And as I was making my way
out of my father's office,

00:08:13.030 --> 00:08:15.080
he gave me the second
piece of advice.

00:08:15.080 --> 00:08:19.730
He said, son, I see
something in you.

00:08:19.730 --> 00:08:24.230
My feeling is that you will do
well in life 10, 15 years down

00:08:24.230 --> 00:08:25.410
the road.

00:08:25.410 --> 00:08:30.740
And when you do well, when you
gain positions and possessions,

00:08:30.740 --> 00:08:33.409
if, for any reason
you think that there

00:08:33.409 --> 00:08:37.850
is one person that you don't
need them because you've either

00:08:37.850 --> 00:08:41.480
outgrown them or getting
a better position,

00:08:41.480 --> 00:08:43.450
that's the day--

00:08:43.450 --> 00:08:46.520
and as an inexperienced
professional, young

00:08:46.520 --> 00:08:48.980
professional, I rushed
to fill in the sentence--

00:08:48.980 --> 00:08:51.870
and I said, that's the
day that I made it, Dad?

00:08:51.870 --> 00:08:53.360
He said no.

00:08:53.360 --> 00:08:56.800
That's the day that
you lost it all, son.

00:08:56.800 --> 00:09:00.280
So the first H in our first
story, my dear friends,

00:09:00.280 --> 00:09:04.510
is H for being humble.

00:09:04.510 --> 00:09:09.460
Understanding that as you
rise up the hierarchy ladder,

00:09:09.460 --> 00:09:16.040
as you taste success,
always remain humble,

00:09:16.040 --> 00:09:18.920
because we are not our
current successors.

00:09:18.920 --> 00:09:21.140
We are not our trophies.

00:09:21.140 --> 00:09:26.170
We are not our positions
or our possessions.

00:09:26.170 --> 00:09:30.700
Which leads me to the second
story that happened in 1998.

00:09:30.700 --> 00:09:34.780
I was one year into
the family business.

00:09:34.780 --> 00:09:38.320
And lo and behold, the company
that my dad told me to take

00:09:38.320 --> 00:09:41.290
care of, which was Carlisle
Food Service Products--

00:09:41.290 --> 00:09:44.430
it's the tumblers where you
have your juice here at Google,

00:09:44.430 --> 00:09:46.270
Carlisle Food Service Products--

00:09:46.270 --> 00:09:49.270
we won the first European award.

00:09:49.270 --> 00:09:52.930
So the Americans told us to
fly all the way to Charlotte,

00:09:52.930 --> 00:09:56.840
together with my brother,
all expenses paid,

00:09:56.840 --> 00:09:58.360
to get our award.

00:09:58.360 --> 00:10:00.040
And we were lucky,
because there were

00:10:00.040 --> 00:10:02.410
seven days of celebrations.

00:10:02.410 --> 00:10:06.070
And on the last day,
Jeffrey Gitomer,

00:10:06.070 --> 00:10:08.710
one of the best sales
consultants in the United

00:10:08.710 --> 00:10:12.360
States, came to speak to us.

00:10:12.360 --> 00:10:16.020
For all those who know me,
I cannot stand still for 10

00:10:16.020 --> 00:10:17.530
minutes.

00:10:17.530 --> 00:10:23.460
I stayed riveted on my chair
for six consecutive hours.

00:10:23.460 --> 00:10:26.730
As soon as Jeffrey
Gitomer finished his talk,

00:10:26.730 --> 00:10:31.230
I ran up to him and I said,
Mr. Gitomer, congratulations.

00:10:31.230 --> 00:10:33.990
How can I become like you, sir?

00:10:33.990 --> 00:10:37.380
And he turned, looked at
me, and said, it's easy

00:10:37.380 --> 00:10:39.060
and it's difficult.

00:10:39.060 --> 00:10:40.990
And as a Cypriot, I
said, what's easy?

00:10:40.990 --> 00:10:44.790
[LAUGHTER]

00:10:44.790 --> 00:10:47.790
He said study on
your chosen topic,

00:10:47.790 --> 00:10:53.540
whichever topic that is,
for two hours every day,

00:10:53.540 --> 00:10:55.550
except weekends.

00:10:55.550 --> 00:10:58.670
In five years, you will be
recognized in your country--

00:10:58.670 --> 00:11:01.610
in 10 years, worldwide.

00:11:01.610 --> 00:11:05.420
I said, sir, I'll start today.

00:11:05.420 --> 00:11:06.380
I bought his books.

00:11:06.380 --> 00:11:09.890
At the time, he had only
two books, "The Sales Bible"

00:11:09.890 --> 00:11:13.190
and "Customer
Satisfaction is Worthless,

00:11:13.190 --> 00:11:16.680
Customer Loyalty is Priceless."

00:11:16.680 --> 00:11:22.900
I even bought his cassettes--
not DVDs, not CDs, not USBs,

00:11:22.900 --> 00:11:24.560
but cassettes.

00:11:24.560 --> 00:11:28.460
And I was listening to
Jeffrey Gitomer's cassettes

00:11:28.460 --> 00:11:33.230
in my car, which was sales
messages coming out, driving

00:11:33.230 --> 00:11:35.930
from one town of
Cyprus to the next,

00:11:35.930 --> 00:11:38.660
promoting Carlisle Food
Service Products and all

00:11:38.660 --> 00:11:40.590
the other products
that we had at Virardi.

00:11:40.590 --> 00:11:44.150
And I was weeping in my car,
listening to the messages.

00:11:44.150 --> 00:11:45.830
And I have a feeling
that people looking

00:11:45.830 --> 00:11:48.305
from the outside thought that
I was going to a funeral.

00:11:48.305 --> 00:11:50.480
[LAUGHTER]

00:11:50.480 --> 00:11:55.350
I still remember my favorite
tape, my favorite cassette.

00:11:55.350 --> 00:11:59.220
It was "101.5
Rules for Success."

00:11:59.220 --> 00:12:02.070
Let me tell you my
favorite rule for success.

00:12:02.070 --> 00:12:04.860
It was the 101.5.

00:12:04.860 --> 00:12:08.810
You're given a bucket of
water and a bucket of cement.

00:12:08.810 --> 00:12:11.420
You can either build
a stepping stone

00:12:11.420 --> 00:12:15.440
toward success or
a stumbling block.

00:12:15.440 --> 00:12:17.855
The choice is yours.

00:12:20.610 --> 00:12:22.470
And he was right.

00:12:22.470 --> 00:12:26.310
Even the great author
Malcolm Gladwell in his book

00:12:26.310 --> 00:12:29.900
"Outliers", he said
the exact same thing.

00:12:29.900 --> 00:12:32.060
He popularized a
notion that wasn't his,

00:12:32.060 --> 00:12:35.030
but it was the 10,000 hours.

00:12:35.030 --> 00:12:38.360
Malcolm Gladwell said that if
you want to achieve something,

00:12:38.360 --> 00:12:41.240
you need to put those
10,000 hours in.

00:12:41.240 --> 00:12:46.370
Even the Beatles were unknown
for seven consecutive years

00:12:46.370 --> 00:12:51.410
as they played music in what
was eastern Germany at the time.

00:12:51.410 --> 00:12:53.930
And it was after they hit
that mark, the 10,000 hour

00:12:53.930 --> 00:12:57.470
mark, that people started
to recognize them.

00:12:57.470 --> 00:13:01.010
Even great criminals,
as it says in the book,

00:13:01.010 --> 00:13:04.340
need 10,000 hours to
perfect their craft.

00:13:08.490 --> 00:13:17.960
So my dear friends, the
second H is H for hard work.

00:13:17.960 --> 00:13:20.280
I know you work at a
technology company.

00:13:20.280 --> 00:13:23.870
And I know that intelligent
work is also important.

00:13:23.870 --> 00:13:29.390
But hard work takes precedence
over intelligent work.

00:13:29.390 --> 00:13:31.010
I guess what I'm
saying to you is,

00:13:31.010 --> 00:13:35.000
sacrifice something today so
you can gain something better

00:13:35.000 --> 00:13:37.680
tomorrow.

00:13:37.680 --> 00:13:40.320
Which leads us to
the third story,

00:13:40.320 --> 00:13:42.270
which I've never
before said in front

00:13:42.270 --> 00:13:44.130
of a professional audience.

00:13:44.130 --> 00:13:45.300
You can cut the camera now.

00:13:45.300 --> 00:13:47.010
I'm joking.

00:13:47.010 --> 00:13:52.530
2006, as a good Cypriot boy
who was working at the family

00:13:52.530 --> 00:13:54.930
business, getting a bit older--

00:13:54.930 --> 00:13:58.650
by the way, I am 46, even
though I look 45, just

00:13:58.650 --> 00:14:01.600
for your information--

00:14:01.600 --> 00:14:04.010
it was time to get married.

00:14:04.010 --> 00:14:08.470
700,000 inhabitants on
the island of Cyprus.

00:14:08.470 --> 00:14:12.190
We invited 4,000 to the wedding.

00:14:12.190 --> 00:14:13.210
And it was almost 1%.

00:14:15.940 --> 00:14:19.090
And the night
before the wedding,

00:14:19.090 --> 00:14:23.660
I found out that my
wife was cheating on me.

00:14:23.660 --> 00:14:24.160
Yes.

00:14:24.160 --> 00:14:25.990
I know, you say such
a good looking guy,

00:14:25.990 --> 00:14:27.100
and she's cheating on you.

00:14:27.100 --> 00:14:28.970
Can you believe that?

00:14:28.970 --> 00:14:30.100
I had the same feeling.

00:14:30.100 --> 00:14:34.130
[LAUGHTER]

00:14:34.130 --> 00:14:35.710
So what did I do?

00:14:35.710 --> 00:14:37.570
I had to think for a while.

00:14:37.570 --> 00:14:40.820
And then I called
everything off.

00:14:40.820 --> 00:14:42.800
My mother was crying.

00:14:42.800 --> 00:14:44.930
My late grandmother
was hysterical.

00:14:44.930 --> 00:14:47.240
What will happen
to the family name?

00:14:47.240 --> 00:14:48.950
What will happen to our image?

00:14:48.950 --> 00:14:50.463
What will happen to your image?

00:14:50.463 --> 00:14:51.630
What will happen to my life?

00:14:51.630 --> 00:14:52.130
I told them.

00:14:55.610 --> 00:15:00.050
The only person who hasn't
spoken, like always,

00:15:00.050 --> 00:15:03.140
and waited and
waited, was my dad.

00:15:03.140 --> 00:15:05.450
So he comes up to me,
and he says Michael,

00:15:05.450 --> 00:15:07.850
let's go to the front veranda.

00:15:07.850 --> 00:15:10.850
The front veranda
in my parents' home

00:15:10.850 --> 00:15:13.940
was where the bad
news were delivered.

00:15:13.940 --> 00:15:18.630
The back veranda was where
the good news were delivered.

00:15:18.630 --> 00:15:20.750
So I go to the front veranda.

00:15:20.750 --> 00:15:24.160
He puts his hand
on my shoulders.

00:15:24.160 --> 00:15:26.870
And he says, son.

00:15:26.870 --> 00:15:29.000
You have guts.

00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:30.920
Actually, the word
he used wasn't guts.

00:15:30.920 --> 00:15:34.580
[LAUGHTER]

00:15:34.580 --> 00:15:38.870
But for this speech
at Google, it's guts.

00:15:38.870 --> 00:15:43.405
When I die, he continued
on, I'm very happy.

00:15:43.405 --> 00:15:44.780
And I will die
peacefully knowing

00:15:44.780 --> 00:15:48.380
that I can leave the company
to your brother Giovanni, who

00:15:48.380 --> 00:15:52.400
has the wisdom and the
patience, and also to you, son,

00:15:52.400 --> 00:15:54.780
who has guts.

00:15:54.780 --> 00:16:00.590
So my dear friends, the
third H is H for honesty.

00:16:00.590 --> 00:16:03.650
And I'm not talking about
honesty from the other person.

00:16:03.650 --> 00:16:05.630
Because you cannot control that.

00:16:05.630 --> 00:16:07.850
It's being honest
with yourselves.

00:16:07.850 --> 00:16:12.650
To take the hard decisions,
even if it pains you at the time

00:16:12.650 --> 00:16:14.210
that you're taking
those decisions.

00:16:18.340 --> 00:16:21.670
And we move on to
the fourth story.

00:16:21.670 --> 00:16:27.340
One year after not proceeding
with the wedding, 2007,

00:16:27.340 --> 00:16:30.460
now I had to find the guts to
go tell my dad that I wanted

00:16:30.460 --> 00:16:33.130
to leave the company and
pursue what you see me

00:16:33.130 --> 00:16:37.420
now doing, giving keynotes,
training, development,

00:16:37.420 --> 00:16:39.960
and consulting.

00:16:39.960 --> 00:16:40.860
I go up to my dad.

00:16:40.860 --> 00:16:42.300
I explain what I wanted to do.

00:16:42.300 --> 00:16:44.320
He says, son, let's go
to the front veranda.

00:16:47.640 --> 00:16:48.950
We go to the front veranda.

00:16:48.950 --> 00:16:51.600
He said Michael,
you can go your way.

00:16:51.600 --> 00:16:53.280
I'm sure you will succeed.

00:16:53.280 --> 00:16:58.050
But if you leave,
Virardi will close down.

00:16:58.050 --> 00:17:01.110
He bought himself 1,100 days.

00:17:01.110 --> 00:17:06.400
I stayed at the family business
for another three years.

00:17:06.400 --> 00:17:11.089
And when the time
passed, I went back.

00:17:11.089 --> 00:17:13.010
My father was a true gentleman.

00:17:13.010 --> 00:17:15.829
He said son, you
will do very well.

00:17:15.829 --> 00:17:17.720
But I would like to
give you some advice.

00:17:17.720 --> 00:17:20.930
Go your own way, but I would
like to give you some advice.

00:17:20.930 --> 00:17:24.410
This is where the
fourth H comes in.

00:17:24.410 --> 00:17:27.800
Always be helpful.

00:17:27.800 --> 00:17:31.850
Deliver value first
or deliver value

00:17:31.850 --> 00:17:34.650
without expecting
anything in return.

00:17:34.650 --> 00:17:36.170
And he gave me two
pieces of advice

00:17:36.170 --> 00:17:38.150
that I will never forget.

00:17:38.150 --> 00:17:43.130
The first piece of advice was
that when you meet prospects

00:17:43.130 --> 00:17:46.130
and they ask you
to give quotations,

00:17:46.130 --> 00:17:48.850
never merely write a quotation.

00:17:48.850 --> 00:17:51.680
Write a self-help book.

00:17:51.680 --> 00:17:55.400
Give them so much value that
they can see their vision.

00:17:55.400 --> 00:17:58.700
Give them so much
material and value

00:17:58.700 --> 00:18:00.950
so they can bring it to life.

00:18:00.950 --> 00:18:05.270
If they decide to come with you,
your prize will seem minute.

00:18:05.270 --> 00:18:07.910
If they opt to go
with your competitors,

00:18:07.910 --> 00:18:11.198
at least you have
built a stepping stone

00:18:11.198 --> 00:18:12.115
towards their success.

00:18:16.230 --> 00:18:19.260
And my father was right.

00:18:19.260 --> 00:18:21.330
And I still do it
up until today.

00:18:21.330 --> 00:18:23.970
Even recently when a
company from New York

00:18:23.970 --> 00:18:28.080
contacted me to do a
culture enhancement project,

00:18:28.080 --> 00:18:30.070
which involved
strengthening the team,

00:18:30.070 --> 00:18:33.030
and it had a 360
degree evaluation

00:18:33.030 --> 00:18:36.240
which means that those
managers were evaluated

00:18:36.240 --> 00:18:40.590
by the top management, by their
peers, by their subordinates,

00:18:40.590 --> 00:18:42.000
and by customers--

00:18:42.000 --> 00:18:44.490
I didn't just write a quotation.

00:18:44.490 --> 00:18:50.340
I even sent a five page PDF with
all the questions, everything

00:18:50.340 --> 00:18:53.120
that I was intending to ask.

00:18:53.120 --> 00:18:55.380
And if I don't get
the job, I still

00:18:55.380 --> 00:18:59.080
know that I added a
value to that company.

00:18:59.080 --> 00:19:01.440
And if I do get the
job, they can come back

00:19:01.440 --> 00:19:03.648
and alter some
questions, change some,

00:19:03.648 --> 00:19:04.940
and even give me some feedback.

00:19:07.670 --> 00:19:11.260
What my father was telling
me is be a trusted advisor,

00:19:11.260 --> 00:19:14.210
not a salesperson.

00:19:14.210 --> 00:19:16.290
And I guess what
I'm telling you is

00:19:16.290 --> 00:19:20.670
transform your thinking from
what can I get from you to

00:19:20.670 --> 00:19:23.580
how can I serve you.

00:19:23.580 --> 00:19:27.180
And the second piece of
advice he gave me that day

00:19:27.180 --> 00:19:31.440
was that, Michael, you
will never be the smartest

00:19:31.440 --> 00:19:33.950
person in the room.

00:19:33.950 --> 00:19:35.550
And my dad had foresight.

00:19:35.550 --> 00:19:37.740
Even though he
died 19 months ago,

00:19:37.740 --> 00:19:40.000
he never knew I was
coming to Google.

00:19:40.000 --> 00:19:42.270
So this guy had foresight.

00:19:42.270 --> 00:19:44.260
And it's true, my dear friends.

00:19:44.260 --> 00:19:47.490
Even if you are one in a
million, in a 7 billion

00:19:47.490 --> 00:19:52.750
population, there are another
7,000 people exactly like you.

00:19:52.750 --> 00:19:55.060
Why should they hire you?

00:19:55.060 --> 00:19:58.300
Recently I was at
Singularity University.

00:19:58.300 --> 00:19:59.920
I took a course there.

00:19:59.920 --> 00:20:02.740
And they have the
same philosophy.

00:20:02.740 --> 00:20:07.750
They were telling us that
engineers, the brightest

00:20:07.750 --> 00:20:11.200
minds, scientists, were
trying to fold protein three

00:20:11.200 --> 00:20:12.880
dimensionally.

00:20:12.880 --> 00:20:15.640
And they were trying
for 15 years non-stop,

00:20:15.640 --> 00:20:17.950
and they never managed it.

00:20:17.950 --> 00:20:20.560
They opened up.

00:20:20.560 --> 00:20:22.250
They open sourced it.

00:20:22.250 --> 00:20:29.510
And in 10 days only, a wife
from the Midwest folded protein.

00:20:29.510 --> 00:20:32.560
So the experts are
the nonexperts.

00:20:32.560 --> 00:20:35.810
The experts sometimes are
outside your organization.

00:20:35.810 --> 00:20:38.740
And it is not a coincidence
that in the book

00:20:38.740 --> 00:20:49.880
of how Google works, it says
on page 175, default to open.

00:20:49.880 --> 00:20:53.100
So if you cannot be the
smartest person in the room,

00:20:53.100 --> 00:20:54.920
you can be something else.

00:20:54.920 --> 00:20:58.930
In my case, I opted
to be the promptest.

00:20:58.930 --> 00:20:59.900
And I have a rule.

00:20:59.900 --> 00:21:01.490
If you go into my
website, you will

00:21:01.490 --> 00:21:07.310
see that I reply back to my
messages with the rule 7, 7, 7.

00:21:07.310 --> 00:21:10.550
I reply back in 7 seconds,
if I'm not doing anything.

00:21:10.550 --> 00:21:12.260
I reply immediately.

00:21:12.260 --> 00:21:14.120
In seven minutes, if
I'm doing something,

00:21:14.120 --> 00:21:16.340
I want to finish
it and then reply.

00:21:16.340 --> 00:21:19.640
Or in seven hours, which is
the duration of a workshop.

00:21:19.640 --> 00:21:22.370
I finish the workshop
and then I reply back.

00:21:22.370 --> 00:21:26.030
I'm not telling you to do
that within this framework.

00:21:26.030 --> 00:21:31.400
But expand it, if you like, to
14, 14, 14, or 21 seconds, 21

00:21:31.400 --> 00:21:33.650
minutes, or 21 hours.

00:21:33.650 --> 00:21:39.710
But refrain from staying
at the 24 hour rule, which

00:21:39.710 --> 00:21:42.740
was invented when there were
telephones plugged on the wall

00:21:42.740 --> 00:21:45.430
and not smart devices.

00:21:45.430 --> 00:21:46.430
And when they were--

00:21:46.430 --> 00:21:50.000
at that time, people
were more backward.

00:21:50.000 --> 00:21:55.730
So my dear friends, the
fourth H is to be helpful.

00:21:55.730 --> 00:22:01.590
Which leads us to the fifth and
final H. And for this story,

00:22:01.590 --> 00:22:06.410
I need to take you to 9/11/2011.

00:22:06.410 --> 00:22:08.720
That was the day that
I married the woman

00:22:08.720 --> 00:22:13.220
of my dreams, the lady that
puts a smile on a daily face--

00:22:13.220 --> 00:22:16.830
on a [INAUDIBLE] on my face--

00:22:16.830 --> 00:22:18.200
and that's Christine.

00:22:18.200 --> 00:22:23.810
And on the 28th of January
2013, she delivered the greatest

00:22:23.810 --> 00:22:27.920
present in our lives, and that's
our six-year-old Rolando, who

00:22:27.920 --> 00:22:30.290
wanted to accompany
me on this trip

00:22:30.290 --> 00:22:34.700
to meet the people behind
his favorite platform

00:22:34.700 --> 00:22:38.870
and that is YouTube,
because thanks to you,

00:22:38.870 --> 00:22:41.510
he observes-- he
meticulously observes

00:22:41.510 --> 00:22:45.110
Cristiano Ronaldo's soccer
moves on a daily-- sorry--

00:22:45.110 --> 00:22:46.175
hourly basis.

00:22:48.690 --> 00:22:50.900
So when we were going to
get married with Christine,

00:22:50.900 --> 00:22:53.060
Christine went to
her grandfather,

00:22:53.060 --> 00:22:56.960
who passed away recently, who
was married to his childhood

00:22:56.960 --> 00:23:01.190
sweetheart for 68 years.

00:23:01.190 --> 00:23:04.478
And she asked for advice
for a happy marriage.

00:23:04.478 --> 00:23:06.770
And her grandfather was very
happy to give that advice.

00:23:06.770 --> 00:23:07.170
I don't know.

00:23:07.170 --> 00:23:08.962
Maybe he was worried
that I would walk away

00:23:08.962 --> 00:23:11.450
from this wedding, as well.

00:23:11.450 --> 00:23:13.460
And he said to her,
Christine, do you

00:23:13.460 --> 00:23:18.200
know what's the secret to a
happy and a long-term wedding?

00:23:18.200 --> 00:23:22.410
And Christine said, what's
the secret, Grandfather?

00:23:22.410 --> 00:23:29.730
He said give 100% to your spouse
and expect zero in return.

00:23:29.730 --> 00:23:35.910
If your husband to be gives
100% and expects zero in return,

00:23:35.910 --> 00:23:40.710
then you increase your chances
of having a happy wedding.

00:23:40.710 --> 00:23:42.360
Think about it, my friends.

00:23:42.360 --> 00:23:45.000
It also applies to
all the other Hs.

00:23:45.000 --> 00:23:48.300
Give 100% to your marriage
or to your relationships,

00:23:48.300 --> 00:23:50.490
and expect zero in return.

00:23:50.490 --> 00:23:54.960
Give 100% to hard work
and intelligence work.

00:23:54.960 --> 00:23:59.790
Be 100% honest, first and
foremost, with yourselves.

00:23:59.790 --> 00:24:04.170
Even if it pains you at the time
you take the decision, take it.

00:24:04.170 --> 00:24:07.860
If you're wrong, admit
it and apologize.

00:24:07.860 --> 00:24:15.060
Be 100% helpful by offering
value to others first.

00:24:15.060 --> 00:24:19.500
And be 100% humble, not because
you will need someone further

00:24:19.500 --> 00:24:22.560
down the line in your
career, but because it

00:24:22.560 --> 00:24:26.440
is the right thing to do.

00:24:26.440 --> 00:24:30.300
So if you're wondering by
now, what's the fifth H?

00:24:30.300 --> 00:24:34.210
The fifth H is H for heart.

00:24:34.210 --> 00:24:37.050
Open your heart
and pour your heart

00:24:37.050 --> 00:24:39.820
in everything and
anything that you do,

00:24:39.820 --> 00:24:42.690
because it's only in this
way that you can move away

00:24:42.690 --> 00:24:46.410
from positions and possessions,
and you move closer

00:24:46.410 --> 00:24:48.840
to your true North.

00:24:48.840 --> 00:24:52.440
And by true North, I mean
that internal compass

00:24:52.440 --> 00:24:56.430
that is helping you to
navigate through life.

00:24:56.430 --> 00:25:00.120
After all, my dear
friends, it is that compass

00:25:00.120 --> 00:25:05.430
that represents who you are as
human beings at your deepest

00:25:05.430 --> 00:25:06.007
level.

00:25:06.007 --> 00:25:06.840
Thank you very much.

