So be conscientious,
do what you do,

00:29:48.750 --> 00:29:50.560
continue being knowledgeable.

00:29:50.560 --> 00:29:52.950
Put in those hours in
what you're doing now.

00:29:52.950 --> 00:29:55.710
But you have to be
honest with yourselves.

00:29:55.710 --> 00:29:58.080
If this doesn't
inspire you, you need

00:29:58.080 --> 00:30:00.810
to take the painful decision
and do something else.

00:30:00.810 --> 00:30:03.900
And I'm not only talking
about relationships.

00:30:03.900 --> 00:30:05.610
AUDIENCE: I wanted to
ask-- you mentioned

00:30:05.610 --> 00:30:09.540
that you had kind of understood
three years before you

00:30:09.540 --> 00:30:13.480
left the company that you
wanted to change career paths.

00:30:13.480 --> 00:30:17.280
So how did you find the
courage to actually leave

00:30:17.280 --> 00:30:21.452
after three years and just
go off and do your own thing?

00:30:21.452 --> 00:30:22.910
MICHAEL R. VIRARDI:
If there scared

00:30:22.910 --> 00:30:26.870
means that I had the
courage, yes, then I

00:30:26.870 --> 00:30:30.110
believed I was preparing
myself for 10 years

00:30:30.110 --> 00:30:33.630
to find the courage to
go and do what I'm doing.

00:30:33.630 --> 00:30:37.310
And from the day that I
decided to go on my own,

00:30:37.310 --> 00:30:39.710
I had to believe in
myself first and foremost.

00:30:39.710 --> 00:30:43.100
I took my father's
advice on board.

00:30:43.100 --> 00:30:44.180
And I was adamant.

00:30:44.180 --> 00:30:46.370
Even though-- and
I will tell you--

00:30:46.370 --> 00:30:49.980
when I went for my first gig
and they asked me, Michael,

00:30:49.980 --> 00:30:52.430
how much do you
charge for a speech?

00:30:52.430 --> 00:30:58.430
At that time, at that time,
it was 1,500 Cyprus pounds.

00:30:58.430 --> 00:31:03.740
And the guy said excuse me,
1,500 pounds for a one hour

00:31:03.740 --> 00:31:04.940
speech.

00:31:04.940 --> 00:31:08.120
Do you know how much your
competitors are charging?

00:31:08.120 --> 00:31:12.290
And he told me two names which
had 30 years of experience

00:31:12.290 --> 00:31:14.480
and they were
charging 500 pounds.

00:31:14.480 --> 00:31:18.150
Why should I pay
you 1,500 pounds?

00:31:18.150 --> 00:31:20.120
And you don't even
have experience.

00:31:20.120 --> 00:31:23.620
And I said, sir, I was
preparing for 10 years.

00:31:23.620 --> 00:31:26.713
And if you don't like it, I
will give you your money back.

00:31:26.713 --> 00:31:28.130
And he threw me
out of the office.

00:31:28.130 --> 00:31:32.090
[LAUGHTER]

00:31:32.090 --> 00:31:36.260
But the next year, somebody
else believed in me.

00:31:36.260 --> 00:31:41.920
I kept the 1,500 ceiling
and they gave me a chance.

00:31:41.920 --> 00:31:43.780
It went on to YouTube,
which is owned,

00:31:43.780 --> 00:31:46.990
I think you know which
company, by Google.

00:31:46.990 --> 00:31:50.320
And thanks to Google,
I commanded my pricing.

00:31:50.320 --> 00:31:52.870
And thanks to the
performance on stage--

00:31:52.870 --> 00:31:56.830
because my father told me, if
you are going on your own son,

00:31:56.830 --> 00:31:58.627
don't put your prices low.

00:31:58.627 --> 00:32:00.460
Because if you are very
good at what you do,

00:32:00.460 --> 00:32:02.440
it will never go up high.

00:32:02.440 --> 00:32:04.660
Or it will take 10
years to go up here.

00:32:04.660 --> 00:32:06.220
Put your prices high.

00:32:06.220 --> 00:32:09.070
Deliver more value
than expected.

00:32:09.070 --> 00:32:10.600
You'll get a lot of rejections.

00:32:10.600 --> 00:32:13.738
But you will get a
chance, eventually.

00:32:13.738 --> 00:32:16.030
And if you are wondering
where will you find the money,

00:32:16.030 --> 00:32:18.070
you can do two
jobs until you find

00:32:18.070 --> 00:32:21.537
the money to go for your dream.

00:32:21.537 --> 00:32:23.620
AUDIENCE: So you're talking
about really believing

00:32:23.620 --> 00:32:28.000
in yourself and continuing
on, as well training yourself

00:32:28.000 --> 00:32:30.550
and learning and
educating yourself.

00:32:30.550 --> 00:32:31.780
And then going for it?

00:32:31.780 --> 00:32:32.780
MICHAEL R. VIRARDI: Yes.

00:32:32.780 --> 00:32:35.523
But I'm a little bit against
the secret and its philosophy

00:32:35.523 --> 00:32:36.940
that think about
it, it will come.

00:32:36.940 --> 00:32:39.220
Think about-- no,
work and it will come.

00:32:39.220 --> 00:32:42.880
Put in those hours
and it will come.

00:32:42.880 --> 00:32:48.040
And always keep
your bridges open.

00:32:48.040 --> 00:32:51.002
My late father used to tell me
always send a Christmas card.

00:32:51.002 --> 00:32:52.960
At that time, they were
sending Christmas card.

00:32:52.960 --> 00:32:54.910
But always send
a Christmas card.

00:32:54.910 --> 00:32:59.500
Always connect with the people
that you meet on the road.

00:32:59.500 --> 00:33:02.710
Because your network will
determine your net worth

00:33:02.710 --> 00:33:06.412
at the end of the day,
not only your abilities.

00:33:06.412 --> 00:33:08.620
AUDIENCE: And I have one
more question, if that's OK?

00:33:08.620 --> 00:33:12.500
You spoke about the
true North of yourself.

00:33:12.500 --> 00:33:16.330
So if you do not mind, speaking
to us about that a bit more.

00:33:16.330 --> 00:33:19.930
MICHAEL R. VIRARDI: I will
speak about my true North.

00:33:19.930 --> 00:33:24.420
Beyond possessions,
beyond positions,

00:33:24.420 --> 00:33:27.000
I agree with my father
that you need to be humble.

00:33:27.000 --> 00:33:30.670
Because what else
is there to be?

00:33:30.670 --> 00:33:34.890
And I find my true
North when I hug my son,

00:33:34.890 --> 00:33:36.840
or when I'm with my wife.

00:33:36.840 --> 00:33:40.710
And I think what powers
everything is the word trust.

00:33:40.710 --> 00:33:43.540
If you trust people
who are in your life,

00:33:43.540 --> 00:33:47.610
you have less tension
and more trust

00:33:47.610 --> 00:33:50.130
to go forward and do
what you need to do.

00:33:50.130 --> 00:33:52.740
You even have allies
within your company,

00:33:52.740 --> 00:33:55.260
within your relationship,
inside your flat,

00:33:55.260 --> 00:33:56.700
or inside your house.

00:33:56.700 --> 00:34:00.060
You need allies, because no
man or woman is an island.

00:34:00.060 --> 00:34:02.780
You cannot do it alone.

00:34:02.780 --> 00:34:03.800
AUDIENCE: Sorry.

00:34:03.800 --> 00:34:05.490
I have one more question.

00:34:05.490 --> 00:34:07.760
How do we learn and
navigate around failures?

00:34:10.659 --> 00:34:13.480
MICHAEL R. VIRARDI: I also
said before that when you lose,

00:34:13.480 --> 00:34:14.920
don't lose the lesson.

00:34:14.920 --> 00:34:17.889
A failure is a
chance to understand.

00:34:17.889 --> 00:34:21.520
For me, when I used to work at
the Virardi family business,

00:34:21.520 --> 00:34:24.219
I always asked, where
did you find us?

00:34:24.219 --> 00:34:27.219
For you guys, you know
where did they find you.

00:34:27.219 --> 00:34:29.170
It's called Google
AdWords and the rest.

00:34:29.170 --> 00:34:32.980
But I used to ask, and
when I fail at something,

00:34:32.980 --> 00:34:34.400
which what is failure?

00:34:34.400 --> 00:34:37.719
If you stand up,
you're still standing.

00:34:37.719 --> 00:34:42.699
You need to ask what went
wrong, contemplate, think,

00:34:42.699 --> 00:34:44.620
look at your offer again.

00:34:44.620 --> 00:34:48.100
Talk to people, even to the
people who consider you,

00:34:48.100 --> 00:34:50.540
in inverted commas, a failure.

00:34:50.540 --> 00:34:52.389
So the best way is asking.

00:34:52.389 --> 00:34:54.909
Like great
contingency is placing

00:34:54.909 --> 00:34:56.942
the questions, more questions.

00:34:56.942 --> 00:34:58.150
Questions are very important.

00:34:58.150 --> 00:35:00.453
You judge a man or
a woman or a person

00:35:00.453 --> 00:35:01.870
by the quality of
their questions,

00:35:01.870 --> 00:35:03.453
not by the quality
of their answers.

00:35:03.453 --> 00:35:04.870
That's how you
deal with failure--

00:35:04.870 --> 00:35:08.155
with lots of questions.

00:35:08.155 --> 00:35:10.030
AUDIENCE: Thank you very
much for the speech.

00:35:10.030 --> 00:35:11.363
MICHAEL R. VIRARDI: [INAUDIBLE].

00:35:11.363 --> 00:35:14.920
AUDIENCE: I was focusing on the
part, your rule of the 7, 7, 7,

00:35:14.920 --> 00:35:18.270
and then also the 10,000
hours that you put in.

00:35:18.270 --> 00:35:20.260
And I mean, you were
working full time

00:35:20.260 --> 00:35:21.640
for the family business.

00:35:21.640 --> 00:35:23.680
On top of that, you
put in 10,000 hours.

00:35:23.680 --> 00:35:27.250
And now you're traveling around
the world giving speeches,

00:35:27.250 --> 00:35:30.970
and you still reply
[INAUDIBLE] 7, 7, 7.

00:35:30.970 --> 00:35:31.970
How do you do that?

00:35:31.970 --> 00:35:34.303
MICHAEL R. VIRARDI: You can
test it tonight if you like.

00:35:34.303 --> 00:35:35.290
Yes?

00:35:35.290 --> 00:35:36.880
I fly Emirates.

00:35:36.880 --> 00:35:42.160
There is Wi-Fi connection
if I'm going transatlantic.

00:35:42.160 --> 00:35:47.780
Yes, I do it because
if you're prompt,

00:35:47.780 --> 00:35:49.430
people attribute
more things to you.

00:35:49.430 --> 00:35:50.420
That you are reliable.

00:35:50.420 --> 00:35:52.010
That you are dependable.

00:35:52.010 --> 00:35:54.470
That you are the one
they should work with.

00:35:54.470 --> 00:35:57.350
And it's also a
differentiator on its own.

00:35:57.350 --> 00:35:59.570
Marilyn asked me, how do
you deal with failures?

00:35:59.570 --> 00:36:03.200
I also should turn the
question on its head.

00:36:03.200 --> 00:36:04.910
How do you deal with success?

00:36:04.910 --> 00:36:09.500
I ask, why did the
American [INAUDIBLE],,

00:36:09.500 --> 00:36:11.150
why did Microsoft hire me?

00:36:11.150 --> 00:36:12.380
I asked them.

00:36:12.380 --> 00:36:15.020
And you know what's the answer
I get most of the times?

00:36:15.020 --> 00:36:16.460
It's not because
you are the best.

00:36:16.460 --> 00:36:19.370
Because I said earlier, if
you are one in a million

00:36:19.370 --> 00:36:22.100
in a 7 billion population,
there are another 7,000 people

00:36:22.100 --> 00:36:24.155
like you which they're
very good and they

00:36:24.155 --> 00:36:26.180
may have a lower price.

00:36:26.180 --> 00:36:30.050
90% told me because you
are prompt, Michael.

00:36:30.050 --> 00:36:31.730
Because you are reliable.

00:36:31.730 --> 00:36:34.220
Because we were in a hurry
to set it up, and I knew

00:36:34.220 --> 00:36:35.870
I could count on you.

00:36:35.870 --> 00:36:37.760
There are other
things, of course.

00:36:37.760 --> 00:36:39.920
You shouldn't stand up here
and talk about theories

00:36:39.920 --> 00:36:41.510
that you don't believe in.

00:36:41.510 --> 00:36:43.700
You shouldn't talk about
other people's stories

00:36:43.700 --> 00:36:48.573
except if that's an example
that you want to aim for,

00:36:48.573 --> 00:36:49.740
to be truthful and the rest.

00:36:49.740 --> 00:36:53.000
So I do it because
it's also in my favor,

00:36:53.000 --> 00:36:55.290
because most people won't do it.

00:36:55.290 --> 00:36:57.230
Imagine if somebody
walks into your house

00:36:57.230 --> 00:36:59.630
and you don't greet them
because you're busy.

00:36:59.630 --> 00:37:00.980
It's impolite.

00:37:00.980 --> 00:37:03.860
Somebody is walking into
your electronic house,

00:37:03.860 --> 00:37:07.070
and they're knocking the door.

00:37:07.070 --> 00:37:09.770
AUDIENCE: Thank you very much
for the speech, Mr. Virardi.

00:37:09.770 --> 00:37:13.133
How would you define success?

00:37:13.133 --> 00:37:14.800
MICHAEL R. VIRARDI:
Excellent question--

00:37:14.800 --> 00:37:19.220
that's why I use the
word elusive for success.

00:37:19.220 --> 00:37:21.430
It cannot be defined.

00:37:21.430 --> 00:37:24.310
And it cannot be so broad
to include all of us.

00:37:24.310 --> 00:37:29.530
Success is a different thing
for every different person.

00:37:29.530 --> 00:37:31.150
If you ask me what success--

00:37:31.150 --> 00:37:34.780
success is Christine
and Rolando.

00:37:34.780 --> 00:37:38.380
Success, for me, is
to live by the values

00:37:38.380 --> 00:37:41.870
that my father instilled in
me, and my mother, of course.

00:37:41.870 --> 00:37:43.930
Success is to wake
up in the morning

00:37:43.930 --> 00:37:47.450
and be happy doing what you're
doing, love what you're doing.

00:37:47.450 --> 00:37:49.810
And if you're not happy with
it, I'm not saying quit.

00:37:49.810 --> 00:37:52.960
But find a way to
be happy doing it.

00:37:52.960 --> 00:37:55.600
And be honest enough
if you are not.

00:37:55.600 --> 00:38:00.070
If it's after six years,
it really pains you?

00:38:00.070 --> 00:38:02.350
Find the strength to move on.

00:38:02.350 --> 00:38:04.150
That's success.

00:38:04.150 --> 00:38:07.300
Because some people tell me,
Michael, you are a freelancer.

00:38:07.300 --> 00:38:09.500
Sometimes you might
not work as hard.

00:38:09.500 --> 00:38:10.000
No.

00:38:10.000 --> 00:38:12.640
I work hard to see
a vision and to go

00:38:12.640 --> 00:38:17.770
after that vision
with no guarantees.

00:38:17.770 --> 00:38:19.470
So for me that was success.

00:38:19.470 --> 00:38:21.610
For you it might
be something else.

00:38:21.610 --> 00:38:23.040
But it's elusive.

00:38:23.040 --> 00:38:26.940
As they say in
theater, you are as

00:38:26.940 --> 00:38:29.400
good as your last performance.

00:38:29.400 --> 00:38:32.940
And in my job, you are as good
as your last speech or training

00:38:32.940 --> 00:38:34.518
session.

00:38:34.518 --> 00:38:36.060
AUDIENCE: I want to
talk a little bit

00:38:36.060 --> 00:38:37.755
about your public
speaking career

00:38:37.755 --> 00:38:40.380
and acknowledge that about half
the people in the Google Dublin

00:38:40.380 --> 00:38:43.600
office don't have English
as their first language.

00:38:43.600 --> 00:38:45.533
So it's a challenge to
speak, but even more so

00:38:45.533 --> 00:38:47.200
when English is not
your first language.

00:38:47.200 --> 00:38:49.740
So can you tell us a little
bit about how you ramped up

00:38:49.740 --> 00:38:50.850
your communication skills?

00:38:50.850 --> 00:38:51.683
How do you practice?

00:38:51.683 --> 00:38:52.480
What are your tips?

00:38:52.480 --> 00:38:53.730
MICHAEL R. VIRARDI: Excellent.

00:38:53.730 --> 00:38:54.230
Very good.

00:38:54.230 --> 00:38:56.790
Because we are also addressing
this on the online program

00:38:56.790 --> 00:38:59.790
that is coming out.

00:38:59.790 --> 00:39:01.500
There was once a
great football player

00:39:01.500 --> 00:39:03.090
by the name of
Milenko Spoljaric.

00:39:03.090 --> 00:39:06.810
He used to play for my
team in Cyprus, Apollon.

00:39:06.810 --> 00:39:11.560
Milenko was a very talented
player, extremely talented.

00:39:11.560 --> 00:39:13.470
He never played in Europe.

00:39:13.470 --> 00:39:15.240
He never played
in the big league

00:39:15.240 --> 00:39:17.270
because he was very slow.

00:39:17.270 --> 00:39:19.250
And he gave me a
piece of advice.

00:39:19.250 --> 00:39:22.680
If you're a slow player,
pass the ball faster.

00:39:22.680 --> 00:39:26.850
The ball travels much
faster than if you dribble.

00:39:26.850 --> 00:39:29.100
So if you are not
a native speaker,

00:39:29.100 --> 00:39:31.680
it's not the fancy words.

00:39:31.680 --> 00:39:36.120
Keep it short, keep it simple,
and practice, practice,

00:39:36.120 --> 00:39:37.245
practice, practice.

00:39:40.090 --> 00:39:42.290
Perfect practice makes perfect.

00:39:42.290 --> 00:39:43.300
So try it again.

00:39:43.300 --> 00:39:44.172
And keep it simple.

00:39:44.172 --> 00:39:46.630
Even with my mentees-- when
they come for coaching sessions

00:39:46.630 --> 00:39:49.840
one on one, even if that
is-- even if they're

00:39:49.840 --> 00:39:51.820
in their native
language is English,

00:39:51.820 --> 00:39:54.280
I always tell them,
keep it short.

00:39:54.280 --> 00:39:55.660
Keep it simple.

00:39:55.660 --> 00:39:58.060
They gave me 45 minutes,
one hour to speak,

00:39:58.060 --> 00:40:00.070
I spoke 30 minutes.

00:40:00.070 --> 00:40:02.230
You shouldn't be
keeping it too long.

00:40:02.230 --> 00:40:05.290
If the people get the gist
of what you want to say,

00:40:05.290 --> 00:40:06.580
it's not the fancy words.

00:40:06.580 --> 00:40:10.160
And think about it, which
is your favorite politician?

00:40:10.160 --> 00:40:14.350
My feeling is it's not someone
who uses language that you

00:40:14.350 --> 00:40:17.060
cannot resonate
with or understand.

00:40:17.060 --> 00:40:21.370
But it's someone who
speaks to your heart.

00:40:21.370 --> 00:40:22.150
Keep it short.

00:40:22.150 --> 00:40:23.110
Keep it simple.

00:40:23.110 --> 00:40:25.650
And practice.

00:40:25.650 --> 00:40:26.680
Thank you very much.

00:40:26.680 --> 00:40:27.972
It was a pleasure and an honor.

